DAMATURU – It was a tumultuous scene at the NYSC Orientation Camp Dazigau, Yobe State as both corps members and camp officials welcomed the Director General of the Scheme Brigadier General Mohammed K Fadah. Addressing the Corps members at the multi – purpose hall, the DG congratulated them on the successful completion of their various courses of study which qualified them for mobilization into the NYSC. He therefore, charged them to participate actively in all programmes and activities particularly the SAED programme in view of dearth of white – collar job. He also informed them of the benefits of self – reliance.  The NYSC helmsman equally cautioned them against indulging in vices inimical to good conduct. Speaking further, General Fadah commended them on their good conduct in camp. Earlier the Yobe State NYSC Coordinator Mrs Hafsat Yerima had told the DG that activities on camp have been going on smoothly. She praised the corps members for their discipline and responding to camp activities positively. High point of the visit was the presentation of cash gifts to corps members by the Director General.